quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  18,60,"And (bring to mind) when Musa said to the young man with him: “I will not give up (travelling) until I reach the junction of the two seas, or I will journey on for ages"
  18,61,"So when they both reached the meeting point between these two (seas), both forgot their fish, so it found its way in the sea, swiftly"
  18,62,"And when the two travelled beyond (it) he said to his young man: “Bring us our lunch. Surely, indeed we have met in our this travel serious fatigue.”"
  18,63,"He said: “Did you mark when we got seated on the rock so indeed I forgot the fish. And none made me forget except the Satan that I may keep it in memory, and it found its way to the sea in a very strange way!”"
  18,64,"(Musa) said: “That is what we have been seehead of state.\" So they both returned in the light of the footsteps of the two, retracing (the overrun site)"
  18,65,"So both of them found Abdan-min-Ibadina (‘an obedient out of Our obedients’) whom We had bestowed mercy proceeding from Us, and whom We had taught from Us, knowledge. [‘Khidr’ has been allotted as a proper name to this person in some man-written books. Many irrational, mythological powers have also been associated to this personality. All these, fake name and imaginary statements, must not act as a barrier in understanding the straightforward Message available in the Divine Verses]"
  18,66,"Musa said to him: “Shall I accompany you for the purpose that you teach me out of that which you have been taught in guidance"
  18,67,"(Abdan-min-Ibadina) said: “Verily you would never have the capacity (to stay) with me in patience"
  18,68,"And how will you bear in patience about what you do not have grasp thereat, in knowledge"
  18,69,"Musa said: “Soon you find me, if Allah (so) willed, a patient one, and I will not disobey you (in any) matter"
  18,70,"He said: “Then if you come along with me, then ask me not about anything till I (myself) narrate to you therefrom the Message (hidden in an incident)"